y on dynamical\nstate is much stronger, increasing by a factor of $\\sim$60% from the 1/3 most\nrelaxed to the 1/3 most disturbed objects, an effect significant at more than 3\nsigma. This is the first observational evidence that the shape of the\nintegrated total mass profile in massive clusters is principally governed by\nthe dynamical state, and is only mildly dependent on redshift. We discuss the\nconsequences for the comparison between observations and theoretical\npredictions.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 5 Jun 2019 22:26:38 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 1 Aug 2019 12:38:00 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-08-14"}
