,\nthis \"rigid picture\" breaks down after a very short RG time. Furthermore, we\nreanalyze, and refute the claim that the huge energy densities one obtains in\nstandard quantum field theory by summing up to zero-point energies imply a\nnaturalness problem for the observed small value of the cosmological constant.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 6 Jun 2019 10:27:21 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-01-08"}
